<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9128> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9128" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 750, footnote 340" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7122> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7122" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. Suff. 45. Shackleton Bailey (CLF 2.434) suggests that he also had the agnomen Sanga (see Fam, 7.30.1; CLA 1.348; and cf. RE no. 143, and MRR 2.490). The connection of Q. Fabius Sanga with the Allobroges (Sall. Cat. 41.2-3) suggests that he was a descendant of Allobrogicus  (110). Cos. 121. His praetorship is listed under 48 (MRR 2.273), the latest legal date. Caesar did advance some (e.g., M. Antonius and P. Cornelius Dolabella) to the consulship without holding the praetorship, but it would be strange after the distinction of Fabius' curule aedileship in 57 (MRR 2.201), if he had not reached the praetorship well before 48,, like several of his contemporaries. See Sumner, Phoenix 25, 1971, 251-252.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6714> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6714" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. Suff. 45 CIL 1(2).2, p. 764, no. 383 d. Grant (26f.) suggests the above identification." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5916> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5916" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate under Caesar in Spain (see 46, Legates; Bell. Hisp. 2.2; 12.2; 41.1; Dio 43.42.1). See above, Consuls." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5893> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5893" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, Consuls, and below, Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5868> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5868" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He entered upon office about October 1, celebrated a triumph ex Hispania on October 13, and died suddenly on December 31 (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 56f., 133, 500f.; Fast. Ost., ibid. 180, 182; Fast. Amer., ibid. 242; Fast. Colot., ibid. 274; Suet. Iul. 76.2; 80.3; Dio 43.46.2; Cassiod.; on his triumph, Act. Tr., Degrassi 86f., 567; Quintil. Imt. Or. 6.3.61; Dio 43.42.1-2, on the illegality of his triumph; see below, Legates; on his death, Suet. Iul. 76.2; Plin. NH 7.181; Plut. Caes. 58.1; Dio 43.46.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5835> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5835" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate under Caesar, who was sent in advance to Spain (Bell. Hisp. 2.2; 12.2; Dio 43.31.1; see below, on Q. Pedius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5078> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5078" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Restored the Fornix Fabianus (CIL 12.2.762, 763; cf. Cic. Vat. 28)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10071> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10071" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Hispania. MRR II.304-5, Itgenshorst no. 267, Rich no. 268." .
